laboratory_examinations.findings: High-density fluid in the pouch concerning for hemorrhagic fluid. No free air or pathologic lymphadenopathy. A large blind-ended tubular structure in the right lower quadrant measuring 17 mm in diameter, most likely the appendix. There is periappendiceal fat stranding. A 9-mm fecalith towards the infundibulum. Enlarged uterus with a 1.2 x 1.8 cm hypodensity likely representing an ovarian cyst. Otherwise, pelvic loops of bowel are normal with no free air.
